modules.description: Generates XML signals from a parsed game view result. Processes structured game data to produce a sequence of XML events. Used to convert internal game state into a format suitable for external rendering or logging.

Processes and extracts data from IGV XML files, supporting parsing of genomic region annotations and track configurations. Operates on structured data including lists of intervals, key-value pairs, and nested XML elements. Used to generate visual summaries of genomic data for analysis tools.

Converts structured game data into XML events for external use. Processes game state into a sequence of XML elements representing signals. Supports logging, visualization, and data exchange with external systems. Example tasks include generating XML for real-time game rendering or storing game progress in a standardized format.
